    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A dashboard-style SPA with three thematic pillars: Policy (MEXT), Technology (Matsuo Lab), and Practice (Pilot Schools). This non-linear structure allows users to explore and compare the different facets of AI in education. Key interactions include interactive tabs for switching between school case studies, providing a more engaging and user-driven exploratory experience than a simple linear scroll. This structure was chosen to better synthesize the distinct yet interconnected presentations from the seminar, fostering a deeper understanding of the ecosystem. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - MEXT Timeline (Goal: Change, Method: HTML/CSS Timeline, Justification: Clearly shows the progression of national policy).
        - Teacher Training Adoption (Goal: Compare, Method: Chart.js Bar Chart, Justification: Effectively compares adoption rates across different municipality sizes).
        - Student AI Perception (Goal: Compare, Method: Chart.js Grouped Bar Chart, Justification: Clearly shows the change in student views before and after using AI).
        - LLM Process (Goal: Organize, Method: HTML/CSS Flow Diagram, Justification: Simplifies a complex technical process for a non-expert audience).
        - School Case Study Tabs (Goal: Compare/Organize, Method: HTML/CSS/JS Tabs, Justification: Allows for direct comparison of different practical approaches in a compact space).
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
